**Location:** Remote


We’re excited to offer a long-term opportunity for an experienced **React Native Developer** to join a team of professional engineers and designers. Together, you’ll be working on a **US-based product** that’s set to make a significant impact on the PropTech scene. This role offers the chance to contribute to a major market and collaborate with top talent in a dynamic environment.


**About Elevated Living Product**

**Elevated Living** has been improving the resident experience for over seven years. We created a single, all-in-one platform that makes it easy for property managers and resident staff to work together. Our goal is simple: to provide the best experience for residents by replacing multiple, confusing apps with one easy solution.


This is a stable, long-term project that continues to grow, and you'll have the chance to be part of its ongoing success.


Our primary technology stack revolves around JavaScript. We use React for the front-end, Node.js for the back-end, and React Native for mobile development.

**What skills are essential to us?**


* 4+ years of development experience with React Native;
* Practical knowledge of VanillaJS and Typescript;
* Experience working with REST API;
* Experience working with Redux/Context API/mobx;
* Good understanding of ECMAScript specifications;
* Good knowledge of GIT;


- English - upper-intermediate+;

**Additional (good-to-have) skills:**


* Experience with Java/Kotlin/Swift/Objective C;
* Experience with CI/CD (Circle.ci, GitHub Actions);
* Experience working with React.js;


Below, you'll find a control question. Please provide short and specific answers - we will discuss the details during the interview:)

**Company Description** 




 Founded by iGaming veterans who have successfully set-up a number of companies. Powered by knowledge, expertise and experience the company is in a growth phase whilst still holding on to that start-up feeling. We are currently operating a few online casinos with Swedish licences and have many exciting projects in the pipeline. 










**Role Description** 




 The person we are looking for would have the following responsibilities:




 ·        Keeping the company’s ledgers updated, working with the group entities in Malta, Sweden and possibly other countries;




 ·        Recording invoices, ensuring that internal policies and procedures are met;




 ·        Assisting with month-end related tasks, including reconciliations, and uploading of journals ensuring compliance with accounting standards;




 ·        Preparation of balance sheet and P&L reconciliations;




 ·        Preparation of payments;




 ·        Reconciliation of bank statements;




 ·        Reconciliation of affiliate commissions;




 ·        Other general accounting duties to support the financial controller and CFO.










 We think that the right person for this role would:




 ·        Enjoy being part of a fun and fast-paced team. Enjoying learning new skills and processes;




 ·        Be based in Stockholm or Malta;




 ·        Have minimum University level accounting, or in the process of obtaining ACCA/CIMA/ACA qualification;




 ·        Have strong organisational skills, attention to details and a positive nature;




 ·        Be confident using MS Office and able to pick up how to use other systems as well;




 ·        Have professional level proficiency of English.










 It would be beneficial, but certainly not necessary, to also have:




 ·        Experience in the iGaming industry;




 ·        Experience using Quickbooks Online;




 ·        Fluency in any additional languages, especially Swedish.










**What we offer** 



* Be part of a forward-thinking, innovative team that’s setting the pace in the gaming industry.
* Work in a collaborative environment where your insights and ideas are valued and have a direct impact on the company’s success.
* Enjoy a vibrant and supportive workplace that fosters growth, creativity, and a shared commitment to excellence.
* Frequent and generous company events.

**Who We Are** 










 Magnit is the evolution of work. Serving hundreds of the world’s most recognizable brands for the past 30+ years, Magnit offers the industry’s first holistic platform for the modern workforce. Magnit’s integrated workforce management (IWM) platform supported by data, software, intelligence, and best-in-class services team is key to our clients’ success. It can adapt quickly to regional or industry economic shifts, and provides the speed, scale, flexibility, transparency, and expertise required to meet an organization’s contingent workforce management, talent strategy and broader organization goals. At Magnit, you’ll work with passionate colleagues who collaborate and deliver meaningful results that positively transform the largest companies around the globe.










**About the Role** 










 You will be responsible for the efficient delivery of Magnits MSP "Managed Service Provider" services to our clients. Based in Sweden, you will be working closely with vendors, client hiring managers and Magnit cross-functional teams, utilizing our award-winning software - VMS to ensure smooth service delivery.










**CLIENT RELATED RESPONSIBILITY:** 




 DAILY:




 • Work directly with hiring managers and/or other relevant customer contacts to facilitate staff augmentation needs and all related transactions;




 • Own and operate operational meetings with dedicated hiring managers and other relevant stakeholders;




 • Prepare job descriptions and requisitions;




 • Review resumes, conduct phone screening, submit candidates to hiring managers for their review;




 • Coordinate interviews with candidates, suppliers and hiring managers;




 • Bill Rate negotiations and evaluation of candidates;




 • Administration related to projects, projects’ extensions etc.;




 • Supplier relations, setting-up new suppliers, informing suppliers about standards, processes and ways of working;




 • Answering suppliers’ and customers’ questions;




 • Daily contact with strategic suppliers on the specific market to ensure a steady flow and pipeline;




 • Serving the client with strategic market insights based on client specific needs.




 MONTHLY:




 • Schedule and conduct meetings with key suppliers to inform about ways of working and to build strong and long term relationships;




 • Support with time chasing and administration tasks related to invoicing;




 • Support Operations Manager/Program Managers with customer related reporting;




 • Participate in operational meetings with customers;




 • Initiate and operate continuous improvement work strategy together with clients and relevant teams to meet the customer plan;




 YEARLY:




 • Support Operation Manager/Program Manager with customer related reporting.










**MAGNIT INTERNAL RESPONSIBILITY:** 




 DAILY:




 • Communicate possible improvements and optimization related to internal processes (including the VMS);




 • Monitor and escalates all issues related to daily operations or internal processes to ensure efficient management and improvement.




 MONTHLY:




 • Join monthly Nordic Staff Meetings;




 • Join the Global Town Halls.




 YEARLY:




 • Engage in at least one internal project per year (i.e. project aiming for internal efficiencies, planning and executing social functions etc.);




 • Conduct and pass any internal educations assigned to the individual.




 GOALS:




 • Together with the program teams, ensure that the first class service is delivered to the clients and suppliers;




 • Become an expert advisor within the area of responsibility;




 • Contribute to the development of internal processes and ways of working;




 • Adds value to clients by providing relevant market insights.




 ABILITIES:




 • Team player with strong communication skills, both verbal and written in English and Swedish (Danish or Finnish a plus)




 • Thorough with attention to detail




 • Ability to structure and prioritize work efficiently




 • Ability to cope with a high pace environment




 • Ability to independently resolve problems in daily operations




 • Ability to support multiple customers in a complex operational environment




 • Ability to fully understand the business and be the expert guide within the client specific area.










**What Magnit will Offer You** 










 At Magnit, you’ll be joining an innovative, high-growth environment and can quickly make an impact to help transform the largest companies in the world. You’ll work with passionate colleagues who collaborate and deliver. Magnit offers all employees the opportunity for growth and development, and we want individuals to fulfill their potential and blaze their own trails!










**If this role isn’t for you** 




 Stay in touch, we will let you know when we have new positions on the team.




 To see a complete list of our open career opportunities please visit https://magnitglobal.com/us/en/company/careers.html










 To do our best work we need different viewpoints. Therefore, we celebrate diversity and embrace inclusion.










 As an equal opportunity employer, we are dedicated to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. We strive to ensure that we maintain a positive and enriching work environment for all.

The TRATON group is one of the world’s leading manufacturers of commercial vehicles and is composed of the brands Scania, MAN, International, and Volkswagen Truck & Bus.




 Scania, together with the TRATON group, is transforming from being a supplier of trucks, buses, and engines to a provider of complete and sustainable transport solutions. As part of this journey, we are seeking a Development Engineer to join our Autonomous Logging team. This role offers a unique opportunity of being at the heart of real-time data collection for our autonomous vehicles, enabling data-driven operations for all our customers.




**Your Role:**
 You will work with a diverse group of experts from various cultures and backgrounds. The team is responsible for all onboard data collection for the TRATON group autonomous vehicles. We employ agile methodologies and are deeply committed to innovation and excellence in autonomous transport solutions.




 As a Development Engineer, you will, together with the team, enable a critical component of the autonomous system, i.e., develop and maintain software and tools to enable real-time platform data collection and offloading to our data lakehouse. Among other things, you will process, encode, and record high volumes of data from multiple data streams and formats; you will leverage optimal data storage solutions; create robust APIs; and design analytics and their visualization for the data collection solution.




**Your Profile:**
 We like people who are team players, attentive and humble with the ability to drive the technical development forward. You have technical experience in the areas of software development, computer science, or a relevant related field. The requirements for the job are as follows:






* A B.Sc., M.Sc., or equivalent in computer science, electrical engineering, or a relevant related field;
* Knowledge and experience with Python and C++ along with a keen interest in programming;
* Knowledge and experience with Linux and industry-standard DevOps tools like Gitlab;
* Proficient in English, both in writing and in speech;


 Extra meritorious is:






* Experience with Agile framework and methodology;
* Experience with containerizing and packaging software;
* Experience with hardware and software integration;
* Experience with AWS;


**Why Scania and TRATON?**
 Scania and the TRATON group offer a healthy, inspiring workplace that respects individual needs and promotes both personal and professional growth. We provide significant opportunities for leadership and development. Our comprehensive benefits package includes performance bonuses, an occupational pension, flexible working arrangements, subsidized meals, and more. In Stockholm, benefit from our direct bus service between Stockholm and Södertälje with Scania Job Express, and access to our Stockholm City office, Scania Sergel.




**Application**
 Your application should include a CV and any relevant certificates. We welcome all applicants and strive for diversity in our recruitment processes.




 Apply as soon as possible, screening will take place on an ongoing basis during the application period. Logical and personality tests may be used in the selection process, and a background check may be required for this role.




**We look forward to your application!**
 For more information, contact Gonçalo Collares Pereira, recruiting manager, at goncalo.collares.pereira@scania.com.




 Get some insights of which you will be a part of: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l34sreA2Mjo




 Explore the future of autonomous development with us and be a part of making history in sustainable transport solutions.
